# Path-based reviewer routing. GitHub automatically requests review from
# the listed owner when a PR touches matching files.
#
# Replace `<owner>` with your GitHub username (or a `@org/team` handle for
# org-managed repos). Delete any line whose path doesn't exist in this repo.
#
# Order matters — last matching line wins. The catch-all line at the bottom
# means a PR with no other matches still gets routed to you.

# Catch-all — every file owned by you unless overridden below.
*                                       @<owner>

# Infra / production-impact paths
/infra/                                 @<owner>
/.github/workflows/                     @<owner>
/.github/dependabot.yml                 @<owner>
/.github/CODEOWNERS                     @<owner>

# Security-sensitive scaffolding
/SECURITY.md                            @<owner>
/.pre-commit-config.yaml                @<owner>
/.sops.yaml                             @<owner>

# Claude tooling
/.claude/                               @<owner>
/CLAUDE.md                              @<owner>
